How to create a good prompt using my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of beautiful (v1ck1li:0.99), a woman as a movie star, hair upsweep updo, sweater off-shoulders, trousers, at a movie premiere gala, dark moody ambience (masterpiece:1.2) (photorealistic:1.2) (bokeh) (best quality) (detailed skin:1.2) (intricate details) (nighttime) (8k) (HDR) (cinematic lighting) (sharp focus), (looking at the camera:1.1), (closeup portrait:1.1)"

USSR style (embedding)

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

Rus

Приветствую, товарищи, эта модель создана для генерации анимешных или полу-анимешных артов около советской тематики, она хорошо работает с чекпоинтами RevAnimated и AOM3, а вот deliberate выдаёт слабенькие 2д постеры.

Не стесняйтесь добавлять более подробное описание

У модели есть три версии: USSR, USSRv2 и USSRv3.

👇🏻👇🏽👇🏿

Первая модель обучена на 10 векторах, вторая на 20, а третья на 35. Соответствующее количество токенов они будут занимать. Результаты у них схожи но я бы предпочёл USSRv3, также я пробовал ставить 75 векторов но результат мне показался неудовлетворительным и я даже не стал заливать это сюда.

Если вы знаете как улучшить этот эмбединг обязательно напишите в коментах! В дальнейшем я продолжу изучать токены сея тематики и соответственно обновлять модель.

Eng

Greetings comrades, this model is created to generate anime or half-anime art around Soviet themes, it works well with RevAnimated and AOM3 checkpoints, but gives weak 2d posters with Deliberate.

The model has three versions: USSR, USSRv2 and USSRv3.

👇🏻👇🏽👇🏿

The first model is trained on 10 vectors, the second on 20, and the third on 35. The corresponding number of tokens they will occupy. The results are similar but I would have preferred USSRv3, I also tried to put 75 vectors but I found the result unsatisfactory and didn't even upload it here.

If you know how to improve this embedding be sure to write in the comments! In the future I will continue to study the tokens of this theme and update the model accordingly.

Age Slider

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

Update May 18th added Older Negative

I developed this age slider to work with my Children's Stories model. Some Stable Diffusion models have difficulty generating younger people. This embedding will fix that for you. It can make anyone, in any Lora, on any model, younger. Even animals and fantasy creatures.

Follow me to make sure you see new styles, poses and Nobodys when I post them. Things move fast on this site, it's easy to miss.

How to use:
Just use one of the positive prompts listed to get the desired results. Use them at strength of 1. That means to put them at the beginning of your prompt or make sure they have the appropriate modifier brackets. Example, for automatic1111 it would be (AS-Younger) or (AS-Younger:1.0). They are stackable, so you can combine them together to help with stubborn models. A negative embedding is also included for extra brute force if needed. There are 4 files to download for younger, and 4 for older, check the version tabs at the top.

These embeddings make people/creatures/characters younger.

  • AS-Young-Neg: Place in your negative prompt at strength of 1.0 to 1.3, generally removes adults from the scene.

  • AS-Young: Place at the beginning of your positive prompt at strength of 1.0 to 1.3. Conceptually teenager, may vary by model, lora, or prompts.

  • AS-Younger: Place at the beginning of your positive prompt at strength of 1.0 to 1.3. Conceptually child, may vary by model, lora, or prompts.

  • AS-Youngest: Place at the beginning of your positive prompt at strength of 1.0 to 1.3. Conceptually toddler/baby, may vary by model, lora, or prompts

These embeddings make people/creatures/characters adult or older.

  • AS-Adult-Neg: Place in your negative prompt at strength of 1.0 to 1.3. This will remove any young people and/or youth from the scene.

  • AS-Adult: (Coming Shortly)

  • AS-MidAged: (Coming Shortly)

  • AS-Elderly: (Coming Shortly)

These are the concepts for the embeddings. Some models, character LoRAs, or embeddings might be too rigid, so increase strength or stack on multiple to get the desired result. Additional prompts may help as well.

Do you have requests? I've been putting in many more hours lately with this. That's my problem, not yours. But if you'd like to tip me, buy me a beer. Beer encourages me to ignore work and make AI models instead. Tip and make a request. I'll give it a shot if I can. Here at Ko-Fi

Токены: AS-Adult

Meiyu Cipher

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

Meiyu Cipher is a person who doesn't exist. You can use her if you need a consistent character. She has a tendency to wear hoop earrings (because her creator forgot to caption them!), so you may need to stick "earrings" in your negative prompt. I might re-train to remove them in future.

Please have a look at other Nobody models for contributions by other folks including those created with the LastName and NBDY tags.

Follow me if you'd like to be notified of future models!

Installation

To install, download the .bin file and then place in the stable-diffusion-webui/embeddings/ folder. Then you'll either need to restart WebUI or tap the Refresh button in the Textual Inversions tab in the Extra Networks tab.

To Use

The trigger word for Automatic1111's webui is MeiyuCipher which you can use in your prompt. (It should be <meiyucipher> for InvokeAI). See the gallery below for some examples.

A note about what I use to generate images

  • My main go-to photorealistic model is Avalon TRUVision V2 but I also might use RealisticVision 2.0, Protogen Infinity, or HARDBlend

  • Many of the images in the gallery use TRUVision for the initial txt2img and then RealisticVision/Protogen for a quick img2img pass with denoising set to .10 - .15 to add some additional skin texture. Unfortunately that first generation information isn't embedded into the PNG.

  • I always use the vae-ft-mse-840000 as my VAE. You can find it at HuggingFace. You can enable the VAE dropdown menu in WebUI by going to Settings -> User Interface -> Quicksettings list and adding "sd_vae"

  • When I use Hires Fix to upscale I usually use 4x-UltraSharp for the Upscaler and enable Tiled VAE which is part of the Multidiffusion Upscaler package

  • If I upscale even further in img2img I'll use a combination of ControlNet 1.1's tile_resample/tile model and Ultimate SD Upscaler

Kylie Minogue (90s)

файл на civitaiстраница на civitai

Kylie Minogue is an Australian singer and actress who rose to stardom already in the late 80s. She's often referred to as the Princess of Pop and is one of the best selling artists of all time. With this embedding I'm trying to capture her looks in the late 80s and early 90s era.

Updated: So... I was having a look at my Tiffany Keller TI, one of the first I published on this site, and I was a bit amazed at how good it still looked. I ran a few tests and man, even if there are some issues (I still upscaled the pics for my dataset back then, and it shows in a little bit of saturation and some slight problems with the eyes)... almost every image I generated with that TI looked awesome, to be honest. I wondered why... What was the main difference compared to my current embeddings? The only possible answer was the vector strength, which in Tiffany's TI case was of 0.198. The perfect vector strength, basically. But how did I manage such vector strength with only 1500 steps, I asked myself... Well, again, there was only one possible answer: the learning rate was way different back then. It was a flexible one and, apparently, it quickly pushed the vector strength much higher than my most recent settings do.

So I decided to try to apply that learning rate to Kylie and stop the training process at 1500 steps. Vector strength is slightly over 0.2, but yeah... the results look great, in my opinion, so I'm probably sticking to this new process from now on. :)

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

How to create a good prompt using my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (t3stkyli3:0.99), a woman, RAW, close portrait photo, long brown coat, (turtleneck sweater:1.2), trousers, curly hair, (high detailed skin:1.2), 8k uhd, dslr, soft lighting, high quality, film grain, Fujifilm XT3 sharp focus, f 5.6"
